    "steps": [
        "Heat olive oil in a pan and saut\u00e9 the chopped onions and garlic until soft.",
        "Add the chicken, ground cinnamon, ginger, turmeric, saffron, black pepper, salt, and chicken broth. Simmer for 20 minutes.",
        "Remove the chicken, shred it, and return it to the pan.",
        "Slowly stir in the beaten eggs until the mixture thickens.",
        "Mix in the toasted almonds, raisins, and sugar, then let the mixture cool.",
        "Layer phyllo dough sheets in a greased baking dish, brushing each sheet with melted butter.",
        "Fill with the chicken mixture, fold over, and add additional phyllo layers as needed.",
        "Bake at 375\u00b0F (190\u00b0C) for 30-35 minutes until golden.",
        "Garnish with powdered sugar and cinnamon before serving."
